Proposed law requires that the Dept. of Public Safety and Corrections (DPS&C), office of
motor vehicles (OMV), issue a special prestige license plate to be known as the "Louisiana
Dental Hygienists' Association" license plate, provided that there is a minimum of 1,000
applicants for such plates.
Proposed law establishes that the plate may issued, upon application, to any citizen of
Louisiana.
Proposed law specifies that the plate is restricted to use on passenger cars, pickup trucks,
recreational vehicles, motorcycles, and vans. Further directs the DP&S, OMV, to create the
special prestige license plate when the applicable statutory provisions are met and the dept.'s
electronic vehicle and registration system is updated to accommodate the creation of new
plates.
Proposed law requires the design include the words "Louisiana Dental Hygienists'
Association" and "Registered Dental Hygienist". Further requires that a symbol representing
the Louisiana Dental Hygienists' Association appear on the left portion of the plate; that the
letters "RDH" appear vertically in the center portion of the plate followed by four alpha-
numeric digits for registration purposes; and that the plate will be white and light purple.
Proposed law specifies that the plate will be issued, upon application, to any citizen of the
state in the same manner as any other motor vehicle license plate.
Proposed law requires that the dept. collect an annual royalty fee of $25 in addition to the
standard motor vehicle license tax imposed in present law and a handling fee of $3.50 for
each plate to be retained by the dept. to offset a portion of administrative costs.
Proposed law requires the annual royalty fee collected by the dept. to be forwarded to the
La. Dental Hygienists' Assoc. and all monies be used solely for the activities of the La.
Dental Hygienists' Assoc.
Proposed law requires the secretary promulgate and adopt rules and regulations as are
necessary to implement the provisions of proposed law.
(Adds R.S. 47:463.243)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Transportation,
Highways and Public Works to the original bill:
1. Remove a provision which limits the issuance of the special prestige plate to
those Louisiana citizens who are members of the Louisiana Dental Hygienists'
Association and instead makes the plate available to any Louisiana citizen.
